article.headline: Nebraska 77, Alcorn St. 53
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP)Ade Dagunduro scored 14 points and Nebraska used a smothering defense to shut down Alcorn State in a 77-53 win on Saturday. Nebraska (10-2) used a 19-3 first-half run to take control of the game. Shang's put-back made it 19-6 with 13:03 left in the half. But Nebraska made just two field goals in the last 11 minutes of the half and took a 36-23 lead into the break Alcorn State (1-11) was able to cut the Nebraska advantage to 10 but no closer. The Braves shot just 33 percent in the first half and turned the ball over 14 times. Nebraska put the game away with a 17-2 run early in the second half. The Huskers went up 51-27 on Sek Henry's dunk with 15:56 left and took a 58-29 lead on Dagunduro's reverse put-back with 13:24 remaining. Nebraska made 12 of its first 16 shots of the second half in building a 66-33 lead. Aleks Maric had 13 points for Nebraska and Jay-R Strowbridge added 10 for the Huskers. Point guard Cookie Miller finished the game with 10 assists and five steals. Anthony Ford led the Braves with 14 points. Alex Owumi had 13 points and Jamal Thompson added 10.
